WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:03.750
♪ Say ♪
 Dre: Jury duty.

00:03.750 --> 00:05.750
♪ Can you see ♪

00:05.750 --> 00:07.120
An American honor.

00:07.120 --> 00:09.500
One of the cornerstones
 of our democracy.

00:09.500 --> 00:11.880
♪ By the dawn's ♪
  A civic obligation

00:11.880 --> 00:13.500
that's a small price to pay

00:13.500 --> 00:15.830
to live in a fair
 and just society.

00:15.830 --> 00:17.960
♪ Early light ♪

00:17.960 --> 00:19.250
But since the government

00:19.250 --> 00:21.500
is too cheap
 to pay for certified mail,

00:21.500 --> 00:24.540
there's no way to prove
 I got this.

00:24.540 --> 00:27.790
[ Shredder whirring ]
  Which is good,
 'cause jury duty sucks.

00:27.790 --> 00:29.250
[ Electricity crackles ]
  Florescent lighting.

00:29.250 --> 00:30.830
Crappy parking.

00:30.830 --> 00:33.500
A one-way map
 to the nearest lunch spot.

00:33.500 --> 00:36.790
But mostly, jury duty
 is sitting in a room all day

00:36.790 --> 00:38.500
with a bunch of weirdos

00:38.500 --> 00:41.000
who live for the opportunity
 to judge others.

00:41.000 --> 00:43.920
String him up!
Shoot him out back!

00:43.920 --> 00:47.170
Ma'am, for the last time,
this is traffic court.

00:47.170 --> 00:50.500
And your left breast
has been exposed for two hours.

00:50.500 --> 00:51.830
My le--

00:51.830 --> 00:52.830
Oh.

00:52.830 --> 00:54.750
Oh, well...

00:54.750 --> 00:57.920
Justice doled out
 at a buck-80 an hour --

00:57.920 --> 00:59.170
you get what you pay for.

00:59.170 --> 01:00.170
How you doing?

01:00.170 --> 01:01.790
That's why I have joined

01:01.790 --> 01:04.120
millions of other
 patriotic Americans

01:04.120 --> 01:06.040
in saying, "Screw jury duty."

01:06.040 --> 01:07.420
Good news, Dad.

01:07.420 --> 01:09.380
You accidentally put this
in the shredder,

01:09.380 --> 01:11.460
but I was able
to reassemble it

01:11.460 --> 01:13.540
and put your juror number
in the online system.

01:13.540 --> 01:16.000
Why?

01:16.000 --> 01:17.120
Why would you do this?
Huh?

01:17.120 --> 01:18.580
Why would you do
any of this?

01:18.580 --> 01:19.920
No need to thank me,

01:19.920 --> 01:22.620
but I also called to confirm
they received it.

01:22.620 --> 01:23.830
They did,

01:23.830 --> 01:26.620
so 7:00 a.m. sharp,
Temple Street Courthouse.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.120
Be there or be square...

01:28.120 --> 01:30.960
and in contempt of court.

01:30.960 --> 01:32.000
Mu--

01:35.290 --> 01:36.330
I have copies.

01:42.750 --> 01:44.500
[ Door slams ]

01:44.500 --> 01:48.330
Oh, there's the face
of a civic warrior!

01:48.330 --> 01:49.620
Look at you.

01:49.620 --> 01:52.040
Yes, look at me.
I'm a weirdo.

01:52.040 --> 01:54.710
You made me a weirdo.

01:54.710 --> 01:58.000
I befriended someone today
who I believe lives outside.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.460
Told me he was gonna
friend me on Facebook

02:00.460 --> 02:02.380
on the library's computer.

02:02.380 --> 02:05.000
Good news is you did it.

02:05.000 --> 02:06.290
So you're all done now.
 No.

02:06.290 --> 02:08.460
I'm not all done.
It's just the beginning.

02:08.460 --> 02:10.919
They chose me.
I'm on the jury.

02:10.919 --> 02:12.750
Moneyball!
High-five!

02:12.750 --> 02:13.710
Ha, yeah!

02:13.710 --> 02:15.040
[ Rainbow gasps ]

02:15.040 --> 02:16.040
Dad.

02:16.040 --> 02:18.250
Rainbow: Dre, come on.

02:18.250 --> 02:20.210
I don't think jury duty's
gonna be that bad.

02:20.210 --> 02:22.380
I missed
my fantasy-basketball draft.

02:22.380 --> 02:23.750
Do you know
how hard it is

02:23.750 --> 02:25.330
to recover
from computer selections?

02:25.330 --> 02:27.960
I have four centers --
four!

02:27.960 --> 02:29.710
I don't -- Is that something --
We don't want that?

02:29.710 --> 02:31.330
Junior:
Dad, it's worth it.

02:31.330 --> 02:33.670
The criminal-justice system
is broken.

02:33.670 --> 02:36.420
Public defenders
have impossible caseloads.

02:36.420 --> 02:39.080
In some states, they only have
about seven minutes

02:39.080 --> 02:41.170
to prepare for a case.
 Seven?

02:41.170 --> 02:42.790
Hey, Junior,
come here for a second.

02:42.790 --> 02:44.330
Come here.
Can you do me a huge favor?

02:44.330 --> 02:45.580
Yeah.
 Shut up!

02:45.580 --> 02:47.540
[ Gasps ]
Oh.

02:47.540 --> 02:49.420
Not today, big guy.
 Get him.

02:49.420 --> 02:51.120
Another insane fact --

02:51.120 --> 02:54.710
97% of prisoners
accepted plea deals

02:54.710 --> 02:57.000
rather than going on trial.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.330
The system needs you,
Dad.

02:59.330 --> 03:01.420
The odds are stacked
against the accused,

03:01.420 --> 03:02.960
who often
lack the resources

03:02.960 --> 03:05.250
required
for an adequate defense.

03:05.250 --> 03:07.920
Somebody's been watching
documentaries again, huh?

03:07.920 --> 03:09.000
Yes, I have.
 [ Laughs ]

03:09.000 --> 03:11.290
More documentaries.

03:11.290 --> 03:14.250
Every time you watch one,
you ruin my life.

03:14.250 --> 03:16.040
Remember "Super Size Me"?

03:17.580 --> 03:21.000
I just saved you
600 low-quality calories.

03:21.000 --> 03:21.960
You're welcome, Dad.

03:25.250 --> 03:27.170
[ Blows ]

03:27.170 --> 03:30.460
Well, I'm not sorry
you have to do your civic duty.

03:30.460 --> 03:34.380
This is a real person
who deserves a fair trial

03:34.380 --> 03:37.080
and is entitled
to a jury of his own peers.

03:37.080 --> 03:39.500
[ Slams table ]
I wish I could kill you.

03:39.500 --> 03:42.620
But that would just send another
poor bastard to jury duty.

03:42.620 --> 03:44.460
Oh.

03:44.460 --> 03:45.920
Junior: Going -- Oh,
I'm hitting the combo.

03:45.920 --> 03:47.420
Nope, nope.
 Can't get out of this one.

03:47.420 --> 03:48.540
Oh, oh, oh!
 No.

03:48.540 --> 03:50.380
Boom!
Got you!

03:50.380 --> 03:52.460
[Bleep] you, Junior.
You killed me.

03:52.460 --> 03:55.500
Hey! Seth! Language!

03:55.500 --> 03:57.120
We don't talk like that.

03:57.120 --> 03:59.420
This is
an "Oh, fudge" house.

03:59.420 --> 04:02.080
Sorry, Mrs. Johnson.
 Whew,
it's been a long time

04:02.080 --> 04:04.670
since I handed down
the punishment of the Lord.

04:04.670 --> 04:07.080
Ooh. [ Sighs ] Black Jesus,
please don't let me...

04:07.080 --> 04:09.080
Hey.
 ...follow through too hard on
the white neighbor lady's child.

04:09.080 --> 04:10.170
Okay.
 No, let me throw it.

04:10.170 --> 04:11.250
No. No, no, no.
Okay, it's handled.

04:11.250 --> 04:13.330
[ Doorbell rings ]
 It's handled.

04:13.330 --> 04:14.540
[ Sighs ]

04:14.540 --> 04:15.830
Hey.

04:15.830 --> 04:17.040
What up, Rainbow?

04:17.040 --> 04:18.579
Hi.
 I'm here for Seth.

04:18.579 --> 04:20.829
We're going
to the Kanye West concert.

04:20.829 --> 04:22.750
Yeah, that feels right.

04:22.750 --> 04:24.920
Seth, let's wrap it up!
 Okay, just why don't you
come on in?

04:24.920 --> 04:26.460
It's Yeezy time!
 Seth: Okay.

04:26.460 --> 04:28.040
Hey, hey, Janine,

04:28.040 --> 04:30.000
can I talk to you for one
little, quick second?

04:30.000 --> 04:31.290
Please don't take this
the wrong way,

04:31.290 --> 04:32.790
but I'm a little bit
concerned.

04:32.790 --> 04:34.960
Your son could have,

04:34.960 --> 04:36.460
like, a bright future
as a dock worker.

04:36.460 --> 04:37.830
Kid's got
a real mouth on him.

04:37.830 --> 04:39.420
Yeah,
he certainly does.

04:39.420 --> 04:41.620
No, no. Cursing is just
a form of self-expression.

04:41.620 --> 04:44.250
I find that
it allows my baby boy

04:44.250 --> 04:46.380
to feel more comfortable
sharing with his mama.

04:46.380 --> 04:47.960
[ Scoffs ]
 Here, watch this.

04:47.960 --> 04:50.290
Hey, Seth, how many kids
in your class are having sex?

04:50.290 --> 04:51.330
-Wha...
-Five.

04:51.330 --> 04:53.330
But not me.
I'm only doing top stuff.

04:53.330 --> 04:54.580
Mm.
 Ohh.

04:54.580 --> 04:56.040
[ Chuckles ]

04:56.040 --> 04:59.830
Well, I obviously
know Junior very well, too.

04:59.830 --> 05:02.330
We are incredibly close.

05:02.330 --> 05:05.250
And without
the use of profanity.
 Mm-hmm.

05:05.250 --> 05:07.460
You do know that he curses
when he's at my house.

05:07.460 --> 05:09.250
[ Laughs ]
That's impossible.

05:09.250 --> 05:11.290
We -- This is
an "Oh, shucks" house.

05:11.290 --> 05:13.080
We don't --
What is that?

05:13.080 --> 05:14.500
Get that [bleep]
 out of my house!

05:14.500 --> 05:15.620
Whew!
 Oh!

05:15.620 --> 05:17.170
Okay.
 Shucks.

05:17.170 --> 05:18.830
Ooh-kay.

05:18.830 --> 05:19.920
On the bright side,
I guess the two

05:19.920 --> 05:21.880
could carpool to the docks
together.

05:21.880 --> 05:23.750
[ Laughs ]

05:23.750 --> 05:24.620
Ow!
 Ooh!

05:26.250 --> 05:27.500
Oh, no.

05:27.500 --> 05:29.540
Don't do that.

05:29.540 --> 05:31.210
♪♪

05:31.210 --> 05:34.210
Okay, so maybe they can
 make me sit here,

05:34.210 --> 05:36.710
but they sure as hell
 can't make me listen.

05:36.710 --> 05:38.170
Narrator: [ Through earbuds ]
  And welcome back

05:38.170 --> 05:41.380
to Andy Richter narrating
 "Rich Dad Poor Dad."

05:41.380 --> 05:43.830
♪♪

05:43.830 --> 05:46.080
Junior: This is not
 just a jury summons.

05:46.080 --> 05:49.500
This is a real person
 who deserves a fair trial.

05:49.500 --> 05:50.290
[ Gavel bangs ]

05:52.790 --> 05:54.210
Judge:
Mr. Antoine Jeffries,

05:54.210 --> 05:56.290
you're charged
with burglary and grand larceny.

05:56.290 --> 05:57.040
How do you plead?

05:57.040 --> 05:59.420
Uh...

05:59.420 --> 06:02.500
Public defenders
 have impossible caseloads.

06:02.500 --> 06:04.620
In some states, they only have
 about seven minutes

06:04.620 --> 06:06.170
to prepare for a case.
 Um...

06:06.170 --> 06:07.460
Guilty.

06:07.460 --> 06:09.290
Oh.

06:09.290 --> 06:10.620
Wait.
That's a different Antoine.

06:10.620 --> 06:13.250
Uh, this Antoine pleads...

06:13.250 --> 06:15.620
not guilty.

06:15.620 --> 06:16.960
Right?

06:16.960 --> 06:19.790
And is entitled
 to a jury of his peers.

06:19.790 --> 06:22.000
[ Yawns ]

06:22.000 --> 06:25.540
Dre: So I was the only thing
 close to a peer for this kid.

06:25.540 --> 06:27.710
Plus I was the only one
 actually listening.

06:27.710 --> 06:29.330
Really?

06:29.330 --> 06:34.040
"Live Free or Die Hard"
is your favorite "Die Hard"?

06:34.040 --> 06:34.830
Ugh.

06:36.080 --> 06:37.500
[ Rainbow sighs ]

06:37.500 --> 06:40.540
I can't stop thinking about
what Janine said to me.

06:40.540 --> 06:41.920
Do you think
Junior's a different person

06:41.920 --> 06:43.040
when I'm not around?

06:43.040 --> 06:45.250
I mean,
I don't let him curse at home.

06:45.250 --> 06:48.620
So am I creating
an environment of deception?

06:48.620 --> 06:50.290
What else don't I know?

06:50.290 --> 06:52.710
The list of what you don't know
is long.

06:52.710 --> 06:55.290
Number one is how
to keep your man happy.

06:55.290 --> 06:56.120
Where's your man?

06:57.120 --> 06:58.710
Hey!

06:58.710 --> 07:00.380
Hi!
How was school today?

07:00.380 --> 07:01.920
[ Chuckles ] Great.
The funniest thing happened.

07:01.920 --> 07:03.420
Oh, tell me.

07:03.420 --> 07:04.880
Wha...

07:04.880 --> 07:07.750
How is it that you just don't
give up on life?

07:07.750 --> 07:09.250
She's -- She's gonna
tell me later.

07:09.250 --> 07:10.920
We're really close.
 Yeah, yeah, right.

07:10.920 --> 07:13.670
Hey! How you doing?
What's going on?

07:13.670 --> 07:15.880
Oh. W-Why -- Why do you have
leaves in your hair?

07:15.880 --> 07:17.790
Well, I didn't punch anyone
in the face,

07:17.790 --> 07:19.250
if that's
what you're implying.

07:19.250 --> 07:20.750
Oh, well, I'd love to hear more
about that.

07:20.750 --> 07:22.540
Well...

07:22.540 --> 07:23.830
Maybe she'll
tell me later.

07:23.830 --> 07:26.210
Oh!
Did one of your classmates

07:26.210 --> 07:27.790
give you
this friendship bracelet?

07:27.790 --> 07:29.420
[ Gasps ] Do you have
a little girlfriend?!

07:29.420 --> 07:31.500
No.
 You can tell me.

07:31.500 --> 07:33.080
Mommy.
[ Giggles ]

07:33.080 --> 07:34.460
Mom,
a little space, please.

07:34.460 --> 07:36.210
Uh...
 Oof.

07:36.210 --> 07:37.880
Oh, my God.
 Mm.
[ Clears throat ]

07:37.880 --> 07:40.000
I don't know my kids.

07:40.000 --> 07:41.460
I'm gonna have to try
the cursing thing.

07:41.460 --> 07:44.380
Mnh-mnh!
Cursing is the devil's tongue.

07:44.380 --> 07:46.500
You're not supposed
to know your kids, anyway.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.420
I hardly know anything
about Dre.

07:48.420 --> 07:51.250
And Rhonda still hasn't
introduced me to her boyfriend.

07:51.250 --> 07:52.250
Ruby.
 Huh?

07:52.250 --> 07:53.460
Rhonda's gay.

07:54.830 --> 07:55.880
Oh, yeah, right.

07:55.880 --> 07:58.120
She -- She's still
doing that.

07:58.120 --> 08:00.330
I don't know why
I even asked you.

08:00.330 --> 08:04.250
An eyewitness
saw the defendant at the scene.

08:04.250 --> 08:08.000
The next day, the defendant was
seen wearing the stolen hoodie,

08:08.000 --> 08:10.500
with a substantial amount
of cash in his pocket.

08:10.500 --> 08:12.880
This is an open-and-shut case.

08:12.880 --> 08:15.790
Antoine Jeffries is guilty.

08:15.790 --> 08:16.830
Thank you.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.290
Mr. Alexander,
the floor is yours.

08:23.330 --> 08:27.000
Look, guys, I, uh...
thought this was tomorrow.

08:29.460 --> 08:30.540
Trust your hearts.

08:30.540 --> 08:32.080
What?

08:32.080 --> 08:35.120
♪♪

08:38.919 --> 08:41.419
Okay, everyone,
let's take a vote.

08:41.419 --> 08:43.120
Get this over with.

08:43.120 --> 08:45.040
You heard the prosecutor --
open-and-shut.

08:45.040 --> 08:47.250
Let's convict this kid
so we can all go home.

08:47.250 --> 08:48.960
[ Jury members agreeing ]

08:52.120 --> 08:52.920
Guilty.

08:52.920 --> 08:53.920
Guilty.

08:53.920 --> 08:54.790
Guilty.

08:54.790 --> 08:55.960
Guilty.

08:55.960 --> 08:56.790
Guilty.
Guilty.

08:56.790 --> 08:57.750
Guilty.
Guilty.

08:57.750 --> 08:58.620
Guilty.
Guilty.

08:58.620 --> 08:59.670
Guilty.
Guilty.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.040
Not guilty.
[ Sighs ]

09:03.040 --> 09:04.380
All right.

09:04.380 --> 09:06.080
11 to 1.

09:06.080 --> 09:07.790
Would the one
like to explain

09:07.790 --> 09:09.540
why he doesn't want us
to go home?

09:09.540 --> 09:14.920
Well, the one,
whoever he or she may be,

09:14.920 --> 09:17.210
might just think
that this is a real person

09:17.210 --> 09:21.080
who deserves a fair trial
from a jury of his peers.

09:21.080 --> 09:25.120
Uh, "open-and-shut"
just seems a little fast.

09:25.120 --> 09:26.750
Great.

09:26.750 --> 09:29.040
All the juries in the country,
and we get the one

09:29.040 --> 09:30.750
with the guy that
just watched a documentary.

09:30.750 --> 09:32.250
[ All sigh ]

09:32.250 --> 09:33.120
What?
 Come on.

09:33.120 --> 09:35.540
♪♪

09:39.880 --> 09:41.040
Rainbow: Okay, guys,
just want to talk

09:41.040 --> 09:42.670
a little bit
about the cursing guidelines

09:42.670 --> 09:45.580
to ensure
a smooth transition.

09:45.580 --> 09:47.920
So you're gonna actually
let us swear...

09:47.920 --> 09:49.540
Yeah.
 ...in front of you?

09:49.540 --> 09:51.960
Yeah! Sweetheart,
words are simply tools

09:51.960 --> 09:53.040
for self-expression.

09:53.040 --> 09:54.580
I don't need
to be so uptight,

09:54.580 --> 09:56.790
and I don't need to be
your word police.

09:56.790 --> 09:58.790
Well, I think
it's a terrible idea.

09:58.790 --> 10:00.460
Yeah, well.
 But you've made
your decision.

10:00.460 --> 10:02.620
Yes.
 I don't know, Mom.

10:02.620 --> 10:04.040
This reeks
of entrapment.

10:04.040 --> 10:04.880
No, no, no.

10:04.880 --> 10:06.250
I promise it's not.
Unh-unh.

10:06.250 --> 10:07.000
Who wants to try, guys?

10:07.000 --> 10:08.000
Come on.

10:08.000 --> 10:09.040
Go for it.

10:09.040 --> 10:10.670
Um...boobies?

10:10.670 --> 10:11.500
Oh.

10:11.500 --> 10:12.960
Oh.
 Okay.

10:12.960 --> 10:14.040
Well, that's something.

10:14.040 --> 10:15.380
Who wants to try the hard stuff,
though?

10:15.380 --> 10:16.500
Come on.
Hard stuff?

10:16.500 --> 10:17.830
-Ugh!
-Oh.

10:17.830 --> 10:19.460
This gazpacho
tastes like [bleep]

10:19.460 --> 10:20.420
Whoa, whoa!

10:20.420 --> 10:22.620
Okay. [ Laughs ]
 It's nasty.

10:22.620 --> 10:25.250
Yeah, all right, well,
that was a little hurtful.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.000
But it sounded
really natural.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.250
I'm sorry, Mom.

10:28.250 --> 10:30.210
I'm just not comfortable
with this.

10:30.210 --> 10:31.420
I don't swear.

10:31.420 --> 10:32.790
Janine's been recording you.

10:32.790 --> 10:34.080
That [bleep]

10:34.080 --> 10:35.670
-[ Gasps ] Oh!
-Oh, my!

10:35.670 --> 10:37.460
Okay, that was so jarring!
[ Laughs ]

10:37.460 --> 10:39.880
But way to go
with the self-expression!

10:39.880 --> 10:42.830
The lines of communication
are open for business.

10:42.830 --> 10:44.670
Ring, ring!

10:44.670 --> 10:47.460
Poop, boobies, snot!

10:49.170 --> 10:50.540
You'll get there,
sweetie.

10:50.540 --> 10:53.040
All right, guys,
a little brainstorming.

10:53.040 --> 10:55.330
Sleep Tite Inns
needs rebranding

10:55.330 --> 10:56.960
because of a series
of recent murders.

10:56.960 --> 10:58.580
Go!
 O-Okay.

10:58.580 --> 11:00.710
Uh, "We know how
to keep a secret."

11:00.710 --> 11:02.710
"Why don't you stay
here...forever?"

11:02.710 --> 11:05.080
"What are the odds
it happens three times?"

11:05.080 --> 11:06.960
"We're killing
the competition."

11:06.960 --> 11:08.500
[ Laughs ]
 Can -- Can I hop in?

11:08.500 --> 11:10.120
Um...

11:10.120 --> 11:12.500
"You'll feel like you've died
and gone to heaven."

11:12.500 --> 11:13.500
Bro.
 Charlie: I see your vision.

11:13.500 --> 11:14.290
Bro.
 I see your vision.

11:14.290 --> 11:15.750
No! Guys!

11:15.750 --> 11:16.880
Guys!
 Did you go to college?

11:16.880 --> 11:19.080
These are horrible,
okay?

11:19.080 --> 11:21.080
All they do
is highlight the murders.

11:21.080 --> 11:22.380
No, no, no, lookit.

11:22.380 --> 11:24.710
We needs something
more along the lines of, um,

11:24.710 --> 11:27.620
"Come for
the endless breakfasts,

11:27.620 --> 11:29.120
stay because
you won't get murdered."

11:29.120 --> 11:30.330
Oh, my God.
I just did it, too.

11:30.330 --> 11:31.580
See?
 You did what we did.

